			<publicationStmt>
				<p><hi rend="bold">Welcome to the digital critical edition project of the Capitula
					to the Octateuch in the Tours Bibles!</hi>
					<lb/><lb/>The editions are part of the PRIN 2022 PNRR project <hi rend="italic"
						>DOBiPS – Data Oriented Biblical Paratext Studies</hi>, awarded for the
					2023–2025 period to the research units at the Universities of Udine (P.I. E.
					Colombi) and Cassino (P.I. R. Casavecchia), under the competitive PRIN PNRR call
					– National Recovery and Resilience Plan, Mission 4 "Education and Research",
					funded by the European Union’s NextGenerationEU programme (protocol no.
					P2022ZW4AW).<lb/> The Capitula prefixed to the Octateuch in the Tours Bibles
					have been encoded in XML/TEI and published using the software EVT (Edition
					Visualization Technology). <lb/>The editions were prepared by members of the
					Udine research unit: Emanuela Colombi, Margherita Filippozzi, and Silverio
					Franzoni. <lb/>Details of the encoding choices and related methodological
					reflections have been presented in the working paper: E. Colombi, M. Filippozzi,
					S. Franzoni, <hi rend="italic">The Digital Critical Edition of the Capitula to
						the Octateuch in the Tours Bibles</hi>, <ref
							target="https://zenodo.org/records/16761174">DOI:
							10.5281/zenodo.16761173</ref>. <lb/>Information on the individual editions
					is available by clicking the 'info' button at the top of the left-hand pane.</p>
			</publicationStmt>
